ORDER

¶ 1 Held: Defendant failed to provide evidence establishing that the circuit court did

not review her evidence, and the ruling of the circuit court was not against the

manifest weight of the evidence.

¶ 2 The defendant, Reba M. Lockett, appeals pro se the circuit court’s judgment for the plaintiff, Darwyn’s Plumbing, in the amount of $6203 plus court costs and against her counterclaim. She argues that the evidence did not support the judgment for the plaintiff and that the court failed to review all of the documents supporting her counterclaim. For the following reasons, we affirm.

